commitResults.messageTitle: Add features to echo user input and exit when 'bye' input is given.
commitResults.messageBody:
- Get user input using java scanner utility.
- Also made minor change to 'breakline' constant as the previous version was not centred.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add the feature to store text entered by the user and display it back to them upon request.
Add ability to mark tasks as done.
commitResults.messageBody: - Created a new class for tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Edit code to adhere to CS2113T coding standard.
Add support for tracking three types of tasks.
commitResults.messageBody:
Types of tasks are:
1. ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park
2. Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm
3. Events: tasks that start at a specific time and ends at a specific time e.g., team project meeting on 2/10/2019 2-4pm

commitResults.messageTitle: Add checker for invalid task indices when marking done.
Refactor code and split code into respective class files.
Add comments and some minor tweaks.
commitResults.messageBody:
- Included comments in Command.java and TaskManager.java.
- Minor change in help message for mark as done.
- Refactored print number of tasks method to be able to reuse when 'done <task number>' command by user is out of range for the index.
